  "prompt": "Who are the best 5 left handed fast bowlers in Indian domestic cricket after Zaheer Khan's retirement?",
  "response": "After Zaheer Khan's retirement, Indian domestic cricket has seen a number of talented left-arm fast bowlers emerge. However, identifying the \"best\" can be subjective and depends on recent performances, potential, and impact. Here are five promising left-arm fast bowlers in Indian domestic cricket post-Zaheer Khan's retirement (as of 2023):\n\n1. **Khaleel Ahmed**  \n   - Known for his pace and ability to swing the ball, Khaleel has represented the Indian national team in limited-overs cricket and has been a consistent performer in domestic cricket. He plays for Rajasthan in the Ranji Trophy and has been a key bowler for his team.\n\n2. **Jaydev Unadkat**  \n   - A veteran in the domestic circuit, Unadkat has been one of the most successful left-arm fast bowlers in recent years. He has captained Saurashtra and played a pivotal role in their Ranji Trophy triumph in the 2019-20 season. He has also been recalled to the Indian national team intermittently.\n\n3. **Barinder Sran**  \n   - Sran, who hails from Punjab, has been a consistent performer in domestic cricket and has also represented India in limited-overs cricket. He is known for his ability to bowl at a good pace and extract bounce.\n\n4. **T Natarajan**  \n   - Although primarily known for his IPL performances and yorkers in T20 cricket, Natarajan has also made strides in domestic cricket, representing Tamil Nadu. He has been a key bowler in the shorter formats and has shown promise in red-ball cricket as well.\n\n5. **Pradeep Sangwan**  \n   - A seasoned campaigner in domestic cricket, Sangwan has been a reliable left-arm pacer for Delhi. He is known for his accuracy and ability to swing the ball, making him a valuable asset in the Ranji Trophy.\n\nThese bowlers have showcased their skills in various formats and continue to be influential figures in Indian domestic cricket.",
